            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA"> 
                <p>To Quintus Avelius Priscus Severius Severus Annavus Rufus, son of Quintus, of Sergia tribe, flamen of the divine Augustus, patron of the municipium, 
                   first of all the Corfinienses to be quaestor for the republic, quattuorvir aedile, quattuorvir for the purposes of administering justice, quinquennial quattuorvir, pontifex
                   of Laurentium Lavinatium. This man, on account of the honour of the quinquennial magistracy, sponsored gladiatorial contests, and on account the honour of the quattuorvirate
                   gave scaenic games, and on account of the honour of the aedileship gave games for the Goddess Vetidina and in aid of the provision of public grain gave 50,000 sesterces for the
                   republic of Corfinium and gave the women's Avelian Baths, along with 30,000 sesterces, and he often distributed public banquets and distributions of money to all the citizens
                   out of his own expenses, and frequently eased the burdens of the republic with voluntary money. The people of Corfinium furnished him (with this monument) at public expense
                   on account of his notable dedication towards his republic. Avelius Priscus, in office, remitted the expense (of this monument)
                </p>
            </div>
